{"1":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.1","c":"وَالنَّجْمِ","d":"wal-najmi","e":"demi bintang"},{"b":"2.2","h":"2.1","c":"إِذَا","d":"idhā","e":"apabila"},{"b":"2.9","h":"3.15","c":"هَوَى","d":"hawā","e":"terbenam"}],"a":{"g":"By the star when it descends,"}},"2":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.4","c":"مَا","d":"mā","e":"tidak"},{"b":"0.42","h":"0.92","c":"ضَلَّ","d":"ḍalla","e":"sesat"},{"b":"1.1","h":"1.88","c":"صَاحِبُكُمْ","d":"ṣāḥibukum","e":"kawanmu"},{"b":"2.5","h":"3.96","c":"وَمَا","d":"wamā","e":"dan tidak"},{"b":"3.2","h":"5.07","c":"غَوَى","d":"ghawā","e":"keliru/sesat"}],"a":{"g":"Your companion [Muhammad] has not strayed, nor has he erred,"}},"3":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.5","c":"وَمَا","d":"wamā","e":"dan tidak"},{"b":"0.65","h":"1.4","c":"يَنْطِقُ","d":"yanṭiqu","e":"dia mengucap/berkata"},{"b":"2.4","h":"3.04","c":"عَنِ","d":"ʿani","e":"dari"},{"b":"2.9","h":"3.75","c":"الْهَوَى","d":"l-hawā","e":"hawa nafsu"}],"a":{"g":"Nor does he speak from [his own] inclination."}},"4":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.15","c":"إِنْ","d":"in","e":"tidak lain"},{"b":"0.43","h":"0.61","c":"هُوَ","d":"huwa","e":"dia"},{"b":"0.87","h":"1.24","c":"إِلَّا","d":"illā","e":"kecuali"},{"b":"1.7","h":"2.52","c":"وَحْيٌ","d":"waḥyun","e":"wahyu"},{"b":"3.2","h":"3.53","c":"يُوحَى","d":"yūḥā","e":"diwahyukan"}],"a":{"g":"It is not but a revelation revealed,"}},"5":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.4","c":"عَلَّمَهُ","d":"ʿallamahu","e":"mengajarkan kepadanya"},{"b":"1.3","h":"2.19","c":"شَدِيدُ","d":"shadīdu","e":"sangat"},{"b":"2.2","h":"3.62","c":"الْقُوَى","d":"l-quwā","e":"kuat"}],"a":{"g":"Taught to him by one intense in strength -","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                وهو المراد بقوله تعالى علمه شديد القوى ذو مرة فاستوى وهو بالافق الأعلى إلى آخر هذه الآيات وفي مثل هذه الأحوال من الصفاء يقع الاطلاع على ضمائر القلوب وقد يعبر عن ذلك الاطلاع بالتفرس ولذلك قال صلى الله عليه وسلم اتقوا فراسة المؤمن فإنه ينظر بنور الله حديث اتقوا فراسة المؤمن فإنه ينظر بنور الله تعالى أخرجه الترمذي من حديث أبي سعيد وقال حديث غريب وقد حكى أن رجلا من المجوس كان يدور على المسلمين ويقول ما معنى قول النبي صلى الله عليه وسلم اتقوا فراسة المؤمن فكان يذكر له تفسيره فلا يقنعه ذلك حتى انتهى إلى بعض المشايخ من الصوفية فسأله فقال له معناه أن تقطع الزنار الذي على وسطك تحت ثوبك فقال صدقت هذا معناه وأسلم وقال الآن عرفت أنك مؤمن\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, this is what is intended by His, the Exalted's, saying: \"Taught to him by one of intense power [shadid al-quwa], endowed with soundness [dhu mirrah], and he rose [fa-stawa] to his true form at the highest horizon [al-ufuq al-a'la]\" to the end of these verses. And in such states of purity [safa'] occurs the unveiling [al-ittila'] of the innermost secrets [dama'ir] of the hearts [qulub]. And that unveiling [al-ittila'] is sometimes expressed as 'discernment' [al-tafarruṣ]. And for that reason, the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said: \"Be mindful of the discernment [firasah] of the believer, for he sees by the light [nur] of God.\" The hadith \"Be mindful of the discernment [firasah] of the believer, for he sees by the light [nur] of God, the Exalted\" was reported by al-Tirmidhi from the narration of Abu Sa'id, and he said it is a rare [gharib] hadith. And it has been narrated that a man from the Magians [al-Majus] would go around among the Muslims saying, \"What is the meaning of the saying of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, 'Be mindful of the discernment [firasah] of the believer'?\" And its interpretation [tafsir] would be mentioned to him, but that would not satisfy him, until he came to one of the shaykhs from the Sufis [al-Sufiyyah] and asked him. So he said to him, \"Its meaning is that you cut the girdle [al-zunnar] which is around your waist beneath your garment.\" So he said, \"You have spoken the truth. This is its meaning,\" and he embraced Islam, and said, \"Now I have known that you are a believer.\"\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"6":{"w":[{"b":"0.04","h":"0.25","c":"ذُو","d":"dhū","e":"mempunyai"},{"b":"0.54","h":"0.98","c":"مِرَّةٍ","d":"mirratin","e":"kekuatan/kecerdasan"},{"b":"2.4","h":"3.12","c":"فَاسْتَوَى","d":"fa-is'tawā","e":"lalu dia cukup sempurna"}],"a":{"g":"One of soundness. And he rose to [his] true form"}},"7":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.23","c":"وَهُوَ","d":"wahuwa","e":"dan dia"},{"b":"0.68","h":"1.16","c":"بِالْأُفُقِ","d":"bil-ufuqi","e":"di ufuk"},{"b":"1.8","h":"2.84","c":"الْأَعْلَى","d":"l-aʿlā","e":"yang tinggi"}],"a":{"g":"While he was in the higher [part of the] horizon."}},"8":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.8","c":"ثُمَّ","d":"thumma","e":"kemudian"},{"b":"1.2","h":"2.11","c":"دَنَا","d":"danā","e":"dia mendekat"},{"b":"1.9","h":"3.09","c":"فَتَدَلَّى","d":"fatadallā","e":"lalu dia turun"}],"a":{"g":"Then he approached and descended"}},"9":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.35","c":"فَكَانَ","d":"fakāna","e":"maka adalah dia"},{"b":"0.9","h":"1.56","c":"قَابَ","d":"qāba","e":"ukuran/jarak"},{"b":"1.5","h":"2.64","c":"قَوْسَيْنِ","d":"qawsayni","e":"dua busur panah"},{"b":"2.8","h":"4.4","c":"أَوْ","d":"aw","e":"atau"},{"b":"3.2","h":"5.1","c":"أَدْنَى","d":"adnā","e":"lebih dekat"}],"a":{"g":"And was at a distance of two bow lengths or nearer."}},"10":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.8","c":"فَأَوْحَى","d":"fa-awḥā","e":"maka Dia mewahyukan"},{"b":"2.4","h":"3.39","c":"إِلَى","d":"ilā","e":"kepada"},{"b":"3.0","h":"4.29","c":"عَبْدِهِ","d":"ʿabdihi","e":"hamba-Nya"},{"b":"4.3","h":"6.16","c":"مَا","d":"mā","e":"apa yang"},{"b":"5.9","h":"6.26","c":"أَوْحَى","d":"awḥā","e":"Dia wahyukan"}],"a":{"g":"And he revealed to His Servant what he revealed."}},"11":{"w":[{"b":"0.06","h":"0.35","c":"مَا","d":"mā","e":"tidak"},{"b":"0.47","h":"0.98","c":"كَذَبَ","d":"kadhaba","e":"mendustakan"},{"b":"1.1","h":"2.02","c":"الْفُؤَادُ","d":"l-fuādu","e":"hati itu"},{"b":"2.3","h":"3.88","c":"مَا","d":"mā","e":"apa"},{"b":"2.7","h":"4.64","c":"رَأَى","d":"raā","e":"dia lihat"}],"a":{"g":"The heart did not lie [about] what it saw.","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                ولموازنة البصيرة الباطنة للبصر الظاهر سماه الله تعالى باسمه فقال ما كذب الفؤاد ما رأى سمى إدراك الفؤاد رؤية\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, to equate the inner insight [al-basirah al-batinah] with the outer sight [al-basr al-zahir], Allah the Exalted named it with His name, saying: \"The heart [al-fu'ad] did not lie about what it saw [ma ra'a].\" He named the perception [idrak] of the heart [al-fu'ad] a seeing [ru'yah].\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"12":{"w":[{"b":"0.07","h":"0.6","c":"أَفَتُمَارُونَهُ","d":"afatumārūnahu","e":"apakah maka kamu membantahnya"},{"b":"2.2","h":"3.78","c":"عَلَى","d":"ʿalā","e":"atas"},{"b":"3.0","h":"4.9","c":"مَا","d":"mā","e":"apa yang"},{"b":"3.5","h":"5.77","c":"يَرَى","d":"yarā","e":"dia lihat"}],"a":{"g":"So will you dispute with him over what he saw?"}},"13":{"w":[{"b":"0.04","h":"0.3","c":"وَلَقَدْ","d":"walaqad","e":"dan sesungguhnya"},{"b":"0.83","h":"1.28","c":"رَءَاهُ","d":"raāhu","e":"dia telah melihatnya"},{"b":"1.8","h":"2.8","c":"نَزْلَةً","d":"nazlatan","e":"satu kali turun"},{"b":"2.9","h":"4.58","c":"أُخْرَى","d":"ukh'rā","e":"yang lain"}],"a":{"g":"And he certainly saw him in another descent"}},"14":{"w":[{"b":"0.08","h":"0.35","c":"عِنْدَ","d":"ʿinda","e":"di sisi"},{"b":"1.3","h":"1.53","c":"سِدْرَةِ","d":"sid'rati","e":"Sidratil"},{"b":"2.3","h":"2.87","c":"الْمُنْتَهَى","d":"l-muntahā","e":"Muntaha"}],"a":{"g":"At the Lote Tree of the Utmost Boundary -"}},"15":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.55","c":"عِنْدَهَا","d":"ʿindahā","e":"di sisinya"},{"b":"1.9","h":"2.66","c":"جَنَّةُ","d":"jannatu","e":"surga"},{"b":"3.6","h":"4.41","c":"الْمَأْوَى","d":"l-mawā","e":"tempat tinggal"}],"a":{"g":"Near it is the Garden of Refuge -"}},"16":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.8","c":"إِذْ","d":"idh","e":"ketika"},{"b":"0.39","h":"1.31","c":"يَغْشَى","d":"yaghshā","e":"meliputi"},{"b":"1.0","h":"2.32","c":"السِّدْرَةَ","d":"l-sid'rata","e":"Sidratil"},{"b":"2.2","h":"3.99","c":"مَا","d":"mā","e":"apa/sesuatu"},{"b":"2.7","h":"4.8","c":"يَغْشَى","d":"yaghshā","e":"yang meliputi"}],"a":{"g":"When there covered the Lote Tree that which covered [it]."}},"17":{"w":[{"b":"0.05","h":"0.4","c":"مَا","d":"mā","e":"tidak"},{"b":"0.47","h":"0.96","c":"زَاغَ","d":"zāgha","e":"berpaling"},{"b":"1.2","h":"2.14","c":"الْبَصَرُ","d":"l-baṣaru","e":"penglihatan"},{"b":"2.2","h":"3.59","c":"وَمَا","d":"wamā","e":"dan tidak"},{"b":"2.8","h":"4.6","c":"طَغَى","d":"ṭaghā","e":"melampaui batas"}],"a":{"g":"The sight [of the Prophet] did not swerve, nor did it transgress [its limit]."}},"18":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.15","c":"لَقَدْ","d":"laqad","e":"sesungguhnya"},{"b":"0.62","h":"0.86","c":"رَأَى","d":"raā","e":"dia telah melihat"},{"b":"1.3","h":"2.06","c":"مِنْ","d":"min","e":"dari/sebagian"},{"b":"1.8","h":"2.79","c":"ءَايَاتِ","d":"āyāti","e":"tanda-tanda"},{"b":"2.9","h":"4.66","c":"رَبِّهِ","d":"rabbihi","e":"Tuhannya"},{"b":"3.9","h":"6.16","c":"الْكُبْرَى","d":"l-kub'rā","e":"paling besar"}],"a":{"g":"He certainly saw of the greatest signs of his Lord."}},"19":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.8","c":"أَفَرَءَيْتُمُ","d":"afara-aytumu","e":"apakah maka kamu perhatikan"},{"b":"1.6","h":"2.85","c":"اللَّاتَ","d":"l-lāta","e":"Al Lata"},{"b":"2.6","h":"4.26","c":"وَالْعُزَّى","d":"wal-ʿuzā","e":"dan Al 'Uzza"}],"a":{"g":"So have you considered al-Lat and al-'Uzza?"}},"20":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.2","c":"وَمَنَوةَ","d":"wamanata","e":"dan Manah"},{"b":"1.1","h":"1.73","c":"الثَّالِثَةَ","d":"l-thālithata","e":"yang ketiga"},{"b":"2.5","h":"3.8","c":"الْأُخْرَى","d":"l-ukh'rā","e":"yang lain/hina"}],"a":{"g":"And Manat, the third - the other one?"}},"21":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.5","c":"أَلَكُمُ","d":"alakumu","e":"apakah bagimu"},{"b":"0.88","h":"2.09","c":"الذَّكَرُ","d":"l-dhakaru","e":"laki-laki"},{"b":"1.8","h":"3.13","c":"وَلَهُ","d":"walahu","e":"dan bagi-Nya"},{"b":"2.5","h":"4.14","c":"الْأُنْثَى","d":"l-unthā","e":"perempuan"}],"a":{"g":"Is the male for you and for Him the female?"}},"22":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.5","c":"تِلْكَ","d":"til'ka","e":"itu"},{"b":"0.62","h":"1.3","c":"إِذًا","d":"idhan","e":"jika demikian"},{"b":"1.0","h":"2.61","c":"قِسْمَةٌ","d":"qis'matun","e":"pembagian"},{"b":"4.4","h":"4.89","c":"ضِيزَى","d":"ḍīzā","e":"tidak adil"}],"a":{"g":"That, then, is an unjust division."}},"23":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.03","c":"إِنْ","d":"in","e":"tidak lain"},{"b":"0.44","h":"0.69","c":"هِيَ","d":"hiya","e":"dia"},{"b":"0.89","h":"1.38","c":"إِلَّا","d":"illā","e":"kecuali"},{"b":"2.8","h":"3.66","c":"أَسْمَاءٌ","d":"asmāon","e":"nama-nama"},{"b":"6.4","h":"7.04","c":"سَمَّيْتُمُوهَا","d":"sammaytumūhā","e":"kamu menamainya"},{"b":"13.0","h":"10.02","c":"أَنْتُمْ","d":"antum","e":"kamu"},{"b":"15.8","h":"13.54","c":"وَءَابَاؤُكُمْ","d":"waābāukum","e":"dan bapak-bapakmu"},{"b":"19.8","h":"17.38","c":"مَا","d":"mā","e":"tidak"},{"b":"19.8","h":"17.76","c":"أَنْزَلَ","d":"anzala","e":"menurunkan"},{"b":"22.8","h":"20.88","c":"اللَّهُ","d":"l-lahu","e":"Allah"},{"b":"23.8","h":"22.36","c":"بِهَا","d":"bihā","e":"dengannya"},{"b":"24.5","h":"23.42","c":"مِنْ","d":"min","e":"dari"},{"b":"25.7","h":"24.5","c":"سُلْطَانٍ","d":"sul'ṭānin","e":"kekuasaan"},{"b":"29.","h":"31.4","c":"إِنْ","d":"in","e":"tidak lain"},{"b":"30.3","h":"32.42","c":"يَتَّبِعُونَ","d":"yattabiʿūna","e":"mereka mengikuti"},{"b":"31.","h":"34.68","c":"إِلَّا","d":"illā","e":"kecuali"},{"b":"32.5","h":"35.6","c":"الظَّنَّ","d":"l-ẓana","e":"sangkaan"},{"b":"34.1","h":"37.44","c":"وَمَا","d":"wamā","e":"dan apa yang"},{"b":"34.7","h":"38.48","c":"تَهْوَى","d":"tahwā","e":"menginginkan"},{"b":"35.5","h":"39.61","c":"الْأَنْفُسُ","d":"l-anfusu","e":"hawa nafsu"},{"b":"38.3","h":"43.25","c":"وَلَقَدْ","d":"walaqad","e":"dan sesungguhnya"},{"b":"39.1","h":"44.49","c":"جَاءَهُمْ","d":"jāahum","e":"telah datang kepada mereka"},{"b":"42.9","h":"47.68","c":"مِنْ","d":"min","e":"dari"},{"b":"43.1","h":"47.87","c":"رَبِّهِمُ","d":"rabbihimu","e":"Tuhan mereka"},{"b":"44.5","h":"50.2","c":"الْهُدَى","d":"l-hudā","e":"petunjuk"}],"a":{"g":"They are not but [mere] names you have named them - you and your forefathers - for which Allah has sent down no authority. They follow not except assumption and what [their] souls desire, and there has already come to them from their Lord guidance."}},"24":{"w":[{"b":"0.04","h":"0.55","c":"أَمْ","d":"am","e":"ataukah/apakah"},{"b":"0.4","h":"1.1","c":"لِلْإِنْسَانِ","d":"lil'insāni","e":"bagi manusia"},{"b":"2.8","h":"4.02","c":"مَا","d":"mā","e":"apa yang"},{"b":"3.2","h":"4.72","c":"تَمَنَّى","d":"tamannā","e":"ia inginkan"}],"a":{"g":"Or is there for man whatever he wishes?"}},"25":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.35","c":"فَلِلَّهِ","d":"falillahi","e":"maka kepunyaan Allah"},{"b":"1.3","h":"2.22","c":"الْءَاخِرَةُ","d":"l-ākhiratu","e":"kehidupan akhirat"},{"b":"2.6","h":"4.32","c":"وَالْأُولَى","d":"wal-ūlā","e":"dan kehidupan dunia"}],"a":{"g":"Rather, to Allah belongs the Hereafter and the first [life]."}},"26":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.79","c":"وَكَمْ","d":"wakam","e":"dan berapa banyak"},{"b":"1.3","h":"2.57","c":"مِنْ","d":"min","e":"dari"},{"b":"2.5","h":"3.69","c":"مَلَكٍ","d":"malakin","e":"malaikat"},{"b":"3.9","h":"5.37","c":"فِي","d":"fī","e":"di"},{"b":"4.2","h":"5.74","c":"السَّمَاوَاتِ","d":"l-samāwāti","e":"langit(jamak)"},{"b":"5.9","h":"8.2","c":"لَا","d":"lā","e":"tidak"},{"b":"6.2","h":"8.8","c":"تُغْنِي","d":"tugh'nī","e":"berguna"},{"b":"7.1","h":"10.12","c":"شَفَاعَتُهُمْ","d":"shafāʿatuhum","e":"pertolongan mereka"},{"b":"8.8","h":"12.74","c":"شَيْئًا","d":"shayan","e":"sedikitpun"},{"b":"14.","h":"13.25","c":"إِلَّا","d":"illā","e":"kecuali"},{"b":"15.2","h":"13.89","c":"مِنْ","d":"min","e":"dari"},{"b":"16.5","h":"16.75","c":"بَعْدِ","d":"baʿdi","e":"sesudah"},{"b":"17.2","h":"17.91","c":"أَنْ","d":"an","e":"bahwa"},{"b":"18.2","h":"19.03","c":"يَأْذَنَ","d":"yadhana","e":"memberi izin"},{"b":"19.0","h":"20.29","c":"اللَّهُ","d":"l-lahu","e":"Allah"},{"b":"20.0","h":"21.76","c":"لِمَنْ","d":"liman","e":"bagi siapa"},{"b":"21.1","h":"23.3","c":"يَشَاءُ","d":"yashāu","e":"Dia kehendaki"},{"b":"23.4","h":"25.71","c":"وَيَرْضَى","d":"wayarḍā","e":"dan Dia ridhai"}],"a":{"g":"And how many angels there are in the heavens whose intercession will not avail at all except [only] after Allah has permitted [it] to whom He wills and approves."}},"27":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.9","c":"إِنَّ","d":"inna","e":"sesungguhnya"},{"b":"1.7","h":"2.17","c":"الَّذِينَ","d":"alladhīna","e":"orang-orang yang"},{"b":"2.9","h":"3.89","c":"لَا","d":"lā","e":"tidak"},{"b":"3.3","h":"4.57","c":"يُؤْمِنُونَ","d":"yu'minūna","e":"beriman"},{"b":"4.7","h":"6.54","c":"بِالْءَاخِرَةِ","d":"bil-ākhirati","e":"kepada akhirat"},{"b":"6.3","h":"8.91","c":"لَيُسَمُّونَ","d":"layusammūna","e":"sungguh mereka menamakan"},{"b":"8.7","h":"11.57","c":"الْمَلَائِكَةَ","d":"l-malāikata","e":"malaikat"},{"b":"11.8","h":"14.73","c":"تَسْمِيَةَ","d":"tasmiyata","e":"nama"},{"b":"12.9","h":"16.61","c":"الْأُنْثَى","d":"l-unthā","e":"perempuan"}],"a":{"g":"Indeed, those who do not believe in the Hereafter name the angels female names,"}},"28":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.87","c":"وَمَا","d":"wamā","e":"dan tidak"},{"b":"0.66","h":"1.83","c":"لَهُمْ","d":"lahum","e":"mereka mempunyai"},{"b":"2.1","h":"3.19","c":"بِهِ","d":"bihi","e":"dengannya"},{"b":"2.9","h":"4.28","c":"مِنْ","d":"min","e":"dari"},{"b":"3.3","h":"4.84","c":"عِلْمٍ","d":"ʿil'min","e":"pengetahuan"},{"b":"4.4","h":"6.34","c":"إِنْ","d":"in","e":"tidak lain"},{"b":"5.8","h":"7.39","c":"يَتَّبِعُونَ","d":"yattabiʿūna","e":"mereka mengikuti"},{"b":"7.2","h":"9.69","c":"إِلَّا","d":"illā","e":"kecuali"},{"b":"7.8","h":"10.74","c":"الظَّنَّ","d":"l-ẓana","e":"sangkaan"},{"b":"9.5","h":"13.85","c":"وَإِنَّ","d":"wa-inna","e":"dan sesungguhnya"},{"b":"10.9","h":"15.49","c":"الظَّنَّ","d":"l-ẓana","e":"sankaan"},{"b":"12.3","h":"17.32","c":"لَا","d":"lā","e":"tidak"},{"b":"12.7","h":"17.98","c":"يُغْنِي","d":"yugh'nī","e":"berguna"},{"b":"13.7","h":"19.49","c":"مِنَ","d":"mina","e":"dari"},{"b":"14.1","h":"20.05","c":"الْحَقِّ","d":"l-ḥaqi","e":"kebenaran"},{"b":"15.0","h":"21.43","c":"شَيْئًا","d":"shayan","e":"sedikitpun"}],"a":{"g":"And they have thereof no knowledge. They follow not except assumption, and indeed, assumption avails not against the truth at all."}},"29":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.75","c":"فَأَعْرِضْ","d":"fa-aʿriḍ","e":"maka berpalinglah"},{"b":"1.0","h":"2.17","c":"عَنْ","d":"ʿan","e":"dari"},{"b":"2.0","h":"3.39","c":"مَنْ","d":"man","e":"siapa yang"},{"b":"2.8","h":"4.37","c":"تَوَلَّى","d":"tawallā","e":"dia berpaling"},{"b":"3.9","h":"6.33","c":"عَنْ","d":"ʿan","e":"dari"},{"b":"5.0","h":"7.44","c":"ذِكْرِنَا","d":"dhik'rinā","e":"mengingat Kami"},{"b":"6.1","h":"9.25","c":"وَلَمْ","d":"walam","e":"dan tidak"},{"b":"6.8","h":"10.1","c":"يُرِدْ","d":"yurid","e":"dia menghendaki"},{"b":"7.5","h":"11.19","c":"إِلَّا","d":"illā","e":"kecuali"},{"b":"8.1","h":"12.15","c":"الْحَيَوةَ","d":"l-ḥayata","e":"kehidupan"},{"b":"9.3","h":"14","c":"الدُّنْيَا","d":"l-dun'yā","e":"dunia"}],"a":{"g":"So turn away from whoever turns his back on Our message and desires not except the worldly life.","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                ولما انكشف لأولياء الله تعالى أن العبد مهلك نفسه بأعماله واتباعه هوى نفسه إهلاك دود القز نفسه: رفضوا الدنيا بالكلية، حتى قال الحسن: رأيت سبعين بدرياً كانوا فيما أحل الله لهم أزهد منكم فيما حرم الله عليكم. وفي لفظ آخر: كانوا بالبلاء أشد قرحاً منكم بالخصب والرخاء لو رأيتموهم قلتم مجانين، ولو رأوا خياركم قالوا ما لهؤلاء من خلاق، ولو رأوا أشراركم قالوا ما يؤمن هؤلاء بيوم الحساب. وكان أحدهم يعرض لهم المال الحلال فلا يأخذه ويقول: أخاف أن يفسد على قلبي، فمن كان له قلب فهو لا محالة يخاف من فساده، والذين أمات حب الدنيا قلوبهم فقد أخبر الله عنهم إذ قال تعالى: \" فأعرض عمن تولى عن ذكرنا ولم يرد إلا الحياة الدنيا، ذلك مبلغهم من العلم\"، فأحال ذلك كله على الغفلة وعدم العلم.\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, when it was unveiled [inkashafa] for the friends [awliya'] of God, the Exalted, that the servant destroys his own soul [nafs] by his actions and his following of his soul's [nafs] desire [hawa]—like the silkworm destroying itself—they rejected the world [dunya] completely. So much so that Al-Hasan said: \"I saw seventy of the Companions of Badr; they were, in what God had made lawful for them, more abstinent than you are in what God has forbidden for you.\" And in another wording: \"They were in hardship more wounded than you are in ease and plenty. If you saw them, you would say, 'They are madmen,' and if they saw the best of you, they would say, 'These have no share [khalāq],' and if they saw the worst of you, they would say, 'These do not believe in the Day of Reckoning.'\" And one of them would be offered lawful wealth and would not take it, saying, \"I fear it will corrupt my heart [qalb].\" For whoever possesses a heart [qalb] inevitably fears its corruption. And those whose hearts [qulub] have been killed by the love of the world [dunya]—God has informed about them when He, the Exalted, said: \"So turn away from him who turns away from Our Remembrance and desires nothing but the life of this world [dunya]. That is the extent of their knowledge ['ilm].\" He attributed all of that to heedlessness [ghafla] and the absence of knowledge ['ilm].\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"30":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.8","c":"ذَلِكَ","d":"dhālika","e":"demikian itu"},{"b":"0.89","h":"1.98","c":"مَبْلَغُهُمْ","d":"mablaghuhum","e":"kesudahan mereka"},{"b":"3.0","h":"4.33","c":"مِنَ","d":"mina","e":"dari"},{"b":"3.3","h":"5.22","c":"الْعِلْمِ","d":"l-ʿil'mi","e":"penegtahuan"},{"b":"4.6","h":"7.95","c":"إِنَّ","d":"inna","e":"sesungguhnya"},{"b":"5.7","h":"8.98","c":"رَبَّكَ","d":"rabbaka","e":"Tuhanmu"},{"b":"6.5","h":"10.42","c":"هُوَ","d":"huwa","e":"Dia"},{"b":"7.0","h":"11.13","c":"أَعْلَمُ","d":"aʿlamu","e":"lebih mengetahui"},{"b":"7.9","h":"12.58","c":"بِمَنْ","d":"biman","e":"kepada siapa"},{"b":"9.2","h":"14","c":"ضَلَّ","d":"ḍalla","e":"dia tersesat"},{"b":"9.8","h":"14.8","c":"عَنْ","d":"ʿan","e":"dari"},{"b":"10.7","h":"15.9","c":"سَبِيلِهِ","d":"sabīlihi","e":"jalan-Nya"},{"b":"12.1","h":"18.19","c":"وَهُوَ","d":"wahuwa","e":"dan Dia"},{"b":"12.8","h":"19.15","c":"أَعْلَمُ","d":"aʿlamu","e":"lebih mengetahui"},{"b":"13.7","h":"20.59","c":"بِمَنِ","d":"bimani","e":"kepada siapa"},{"b":"14.3","h":"21.57","c":"اهْتَدَى","d":"ih'tadā","e":"mendapat petunjuk"}],"a":{"g":"That is their sum of knowledge. Indeed, your Lord is most knowing of who strays from His way, and He is most knowing of who is guided."}},"31":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.47","c":"وَلِلَّهِ","d":"walillahi","e":"dan kepunyaan Allah"},{"b":"1.4","h":"2.18","c":"مَا","d":"mā","e":"apa yang"},{"b":"1.7","h":"2.83","c":"فِي","d":"fī","e":"ada di"},{"b":"2.0","h":"3.17","c":"السَّمَاوَاتِ","d":"l-samāwāti","e":"langit(jamak)"},{"b":"3.6","h":"5.58","c":"وَمَا","d":"wamā","e":"dan apa yang"},{"b":"4.3","h":"6.59","c":"فِي","d":"fī","e":"ada di"},{"b":"4.6","h":"7.06","c":"الْأَرْضِ","d":"l-arḍi","e":"bumi"},{"b":"5.5","h":"10.05","c":"لِيَجْزِيَ","d":"liyajziya","e":"Dia akan memberi balasan"},{"b":"6.7","h":"11.49","c":"الَّذِينَ","d":"alladhīna","e":"orang-orang yang"},{"b":"7.8","h":"13.12","c":"أَسَاءُوا","d":"asāū","e":"mereka berbuat jahat"},{"b":"10.8","h":"15.69","c":"بِمَا","d":"bimā","e":"terhadap apa"},{"b":"11.4","h":"16.5","c":"عَمِلُوا","d":"ʿamilū","e":"mereka kerjakan"},{"b":"12.5","h":"18.1","c":"وَيَجْزِيَ","d":"wayajziya","e":"dan dia akan memberi balasan"},{"b":"13.5","h":"19.55","c":"الَّذِينَ","d":"alladhīna","e":"orang-orang yang"},{"b":"14.7","h":"21.23","c":"أَحْسَنُوا","d":"aḥsanū","e":"mereka berbuat baik"},{"b":"15.8","h":"22.92","c":"بِالْحُسْنَى","d":"bil-ḥus'nā","e":"denganyang lebih baik"}],"a":{"g":"And to Allah belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is in the earth - that He may recompense those who do evil with [the penalty of] what they have done and recompense those who do good with the best [reward] -","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                هنالك تجزى كل نفس بما كسبت إن الله عز وجل يقول \"ليجزى الذي أساءوا بما عملوا ويجزى الذي أحسنوا بالحسنى\"\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, there, every soul [nafs] will be recompensed for what it has earned. Indeed, Allah, the Mighty and Majestic, says: \"That He may recompense those who did evil for what they did, and recompense those who did good with the best [al-husna].\"\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"32":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.75","c":"الَّذِينَ","d":"alladhīna","e":"orang-orang yang"},{"b":"1.2","h":"2.47","c":"يَجْتَنِبُونَ","d":"yajtanibūna","e":"mereka menjauhi"},{"b":"2.8","h":"4.77","c":"كَبَائِرَ","d":"kabāira","e":"besar"},{"b":"5.5","h":"7.11","c":"الْإِثْمِ","d":"l-ith'mi","e":"dosa"},{"b":"6.4","h":"8.37","c":"وَالْفَوَاحِشَ","d":"wal-fawāḥisha","e":"dan perbuatan keji"},{"b":"8.0","h":"10.76","c":"إِلَّا","d":"illā","e":"kecuali"},{"b":"8.7","h":"11.7","c":"اللَّمَمَ","d":"l-lamama","e":"teringat sepintas lalu"},{"b":"10.1","h":"16","c":"إِنَّ","d":"inna","e":"sesungguhnya"},{"b":"11.4","h":"17.3","c":"رَبَّكَ","d":"rabbaka","e":"Tuhanmu"},{"b":"12.3","h":"18.7","c":"وَاسِعُ","d":"wāsiʿu","e":"Maha Luas"},{"b":"13.2","h":"20.15","c":"الْمَغْفِرَةِ","d":"l-maghfirati","e":"ampunan"},{"b":"15.1","h":"24.15","c":"هُوَ","d":"huwa","e":"Dia"},{"b":"15.5","h":"24.66","c":"أَعْلَمُ","d":"aʿlamu","e":"lebih mengetahui"},{"b":"16.3","h":"25.94","c":"بِكُمْ","d":"bikum","e":"dengan/untuk kalian"},{"b":"17.0","h":"26.9","c":"إِذْ","d":"idh","e":"ketika"},{"b":"17.","h":"27.43","c":"أَنْشَأَكُمْ","d":"ansha-akum","e":"Dia menjadikan kamu"},{"b":"20.0","h":"30.43","c":"مِنَ","d":"mina","e":"dari"},{"b":"20.3","h":"30.93","c":"الْأَرْضِ","d":"l-arḍi","e":"bumi"},{"b":"21.3","h":"32.23","c":"وَإِذْ","d":"wa-idh","e":"dan ketika"},{"b":"21.9","h":"33.13","c":"أَنْتُمْ","d":"antum","e":"kamu"},{"b":"23.5","h":"35.13","c":"أَجِنَّةٌ","d":"ajinnatun","e":"janin"},{"b":"25.9","h":"37.74","c":"فِي","d":"fī","e":"dalam"},{"b":"26.4","h":"38.53","c":"بُطُونِ","d":"buṭūni","e":"perut"},{"b":"27.4","h":"40.89","c":"أُمَّهَاتِكُمْ","d":"ummahātikum","e":"ibu-ibu kamu"},{"b":"30.5","h":"46.4","c":"فَلَا","d":"falā","e":"maka jangan"},{"b":"31.1","h":"47.22","c":"تُزَكُّوا","d":"tuzakkū","e":"kamu menganggap suci"},{"b":"34.1","h":"50.09","c":"أَنْفُسَكُمْ","d":"anfusakum","e":"diri kalian sendiri"},{"b":"36.","h":"54.5","c":"هُوَ","d":"huwa","e":"Dia"},{"b":"37.","h":"54.97","c":"أَعْلَمُ","d":"aʿlamu","e":"lebih mengetahui"},{"b":"37.9","h":"56.24","c":"بِمَنِ","d":"bimani","e":"dengan siapa"},{"b":"38.6","h":"57.11","c":"اتَّقَى","d":"ittaqā","e":"yang bertakwa"}],"a":{"g":"Those who avoid the major sins and immoralities, only [committing] slight ones. Indeed, your Lord is vast in forgiveness. He was most knowing of you when He produced you from the earth and when you were fetuses in the wombs of your mothers. So do not claim yourselves to be pure; He is most knowing of who fears Him.","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                بيان ذم العجب وآفاته اعلم أن العجب مذموم في كتاب الله تعالى وسنة رسوله ﭬ. وقد قال تعالى: \"فلا تزكوا أنفسكم\" قال ابن جريج: معناه إذا عملت خيراً فلا تقل عملت. وقال زيد بن أسلم. لا تبروها، أي لا تعتقدوا أنها بارة وهو معنى العجب. وقد قال تعالى \"لا تبطلوا صدقاتكم بالمن والأذى\" والمن نتيجة استعظام الصدقة، واستعظام العمل هو العجب. فظهر بهذا أن العجب مذموم جداً.\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, the explanation of the censure of self-admiration [al-'ujb] and its destructive consequences. Know that self-admiration [al-'ujb] is censured in the Book of Allah, the Most High, and the Sunnah of His Messenger, peace be upon him. And He, the Most High, has said: \"So do not claim purity for yourselves [fa la tuzakku anfusakum].\" Ibn Jurayj said: Its meaning is, when you perform a good deed, do not say, 'I performed it.' And Zayd ibn Aslam said: Do not declare them righteous, meaning do not believe they are righteous, and this is the meaning of self-admiration [al-'ujb]. And He, the Most High, has said: \"Do not invalidate your charities with reminders of your generosity [al-mann] or injury.\" And the reminder of generosity [al-mann] is the result of magnifying the charity, and magnifying the deed is self-admiration [al-'ujb]. Thus, it becomes clear by this that self-admiration [al-'ujb] is most severely censured.\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"33":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.55","c":"أَفَرَءَيْتَ","d":"afara-ayta","e":"maka apakah kamu memperhatikan"},{"b":"1.2","h":"2.25","c":"الَّذِي","d":"alladhī","e":"orang yang"},{"b":"2.1","h":"3.52","c":"تَوَلَّى","d":"tawallā","e":"dia berpaling"}],"a":{"g":"Have you seen the one who turned away"}},"34":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.35","c":"وَأَعْطَى","d":"wa-aʿṭā","e":"dan Dia memberi"},{"b":"1.0","h":"1.9","c":"قَلِيلًا","d":"qalīlan","e":"sedikit"},{"b":"1.9","h":"3.34","c":"وَأَكْدَى","d":"wa-akdā","e":"dan Dia menahan/tidak memberi"}],"a":{"g":"And gave a little and [then] refrained?"}},"35":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.35","c":"أَعِنْدَهُ","d":"aʿindahu","e":"apakah di sisi"},{"b":"1.8","h":"2.47","c":"عِلْمُ","d":"ʿil'mu","e":"pengetahuan"},{"b":"2.5","h":"3.52","c":"الْغَيْبِ","d":"l-ghaybi","e":"gaib"},{"b":"3.3","h":"4.92","c":"فَهُوَ","d":"fahuwa","e":"maka dia"},{"b":"4.0","h":"6","c":"يَرَى","d":"yarā","e":"dia melihat"}],"a":{"g":"Does he have knowledge of the unseen, so he sees?"}},"36":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"1.15","c":"أَمْ","d":"am","e":"ataukah/apakah"},{"b":"0.38","h":"1.59","c":"لَمْ","d":"lam","e":"belum"},{"b":"0.79","h":"2.16","c":"يُنَبَّأْ","d":"yunabba","e":"diberitakan dia"},{"b":"1.7","h":"3.74","c":"بِمَا","d":"bimā","e":"dengan apa"},{"b":"2.4","h":"4.79","c":"فِي","d":"fī","e":"dalam"},{"b":"2.9","h":"5.53","c":"صُحُفِ","d":"ṣuḥufi","e":"lembaran-lembaran"},{"b":"3.6","h":"6.61","c":"مُوسَى","d":"mūsā","e":"Musa"}],"a":{"g":"Or has he not been informed of what was in the scriptures of Moses","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                وقال زياد خلوا سبيله، هذا رجل قد لقن حجته.\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                And Ziyad said, \"Leave his way, for this is a man whose argument has been instilled [luqqina hujjatuhu].\"\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"37":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"1","c":"وَإِبْرَاهِيمَ","d":"wa-ib'rāhīma","e":"dan Ibrahim"},{"b":"1.6","h":"3.42","c":"الَّذِي","d":"alladhī","e":"yang"},{"b":"2.5","h":"4.83","c":"وَفَّى","d":"waffā","e":"dia sempurnakan"}],"a":{"g":"And [of] Abraham, who fulfilled [his obligations] -","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                وروي أنه لما قال جبريل لإبراهيم عليهما السلام وقد رمي إلى النار بالمنجنيق: ألك حاجة؟ قال: أما إليك فلا، وفاءً بقوله حسبي الله ونعم الوكيل، إذا قال ذلك حين أخذ ليرمى، فأنزل الله تعالى: \" وإبراهيم الذي وفى \".\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, it is narrated that when Gabriel [Jibril], peace be upon them both, said to Abraham [Ibrahim] as he was catapulted into the fire, \"Do you have any need?\" he replied, \"Not from you,\" fulfilling his statement, \"Sufficient for me is Allah [Allah], and He is the best Disposer of affairs [al-Wakil],\" which he had said when he was taken to be thrown. Then Allah, the Exalted, revealed: \"And [of] Abraham who fulfilled [wa-Ibrahim alladhi waffa].\"\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"38":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.65","c":"أَلَّا","d":"allā","e":"bahwa tidak"},{"b":"0.8","h":"1.84","c":"تَزِرُ","d":"taziru","e":"kamu memikul dosa"},{"b":"1.5","h":"2.97","c":"وَازِرَةٌ","d":"wāziratun","e":"orang yang berdosa"},{"b":"3.4","h":"5.35","c":"وِزْرَ","d":"wiz'ra","e":"beban/dosa"},{"b":"4.1","h":"6.33","c":"أُخْرَى","d":"ukh'rā","e":"orang lain"}],"a":{"g":"That no bearer of burdens will bear the burden of another"}},"39":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.85","c":"وَأَنْ","d":"wa-an","e":"dan bahwa"},{"b":"0.33","h":"1.33","c":"لَيْسَ","d":"laysa","e":"tidak"},{"b":"1.2","h":"2.74","c":"لِلْإِنْسَانِ","d":"lil'insāni","e":"bagi manusia"},{"b":"3.6","h":"5.64","c":"إِلَّا","d":"illā","e":"kecuali"},{"b":"4.5","h":"7.03","c":"مَا","d":"mā","e":"apa yang"},{"b":"4.8","h":"7.83","c":"سَعَى","d":"saʿā","e":"ia usahakan"}],"a":{"g":"And that there is not for man except that [good] for which he strives","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                وقال في أمر الآخرة وأن ليس للإنسان إلا ما سعى فقد تكفل لك بأمر الدنيا خاصة وصرفك عن السعى فيها فكذبته بأفعالك وأصبحت تتكالبين على طلبها تكالب المدهوش المستهتر ووكل أمر الآخرة إلى سعيك فأعرضت عنها إعراض المغرور المستحقر.\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, concerning the matter of the Hereafter [al-akhirah] and that for man there is only what he strives for, He has guaranteed for you the matter of the world [al-dunya] specifically and diverted you from striving in it. Yet you have belied Him with your actions, and you have become one who scrambles in pursuit of it, scrambling like one who is bewildered and heedless. And He has entrusted the matter of the Hereafter [al-akhirah] to your striving, yet you have turned away from it, turning away like one who is deluded and contemptuous.\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"40":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.85","c":"وَأَنَّ","d":"wa-anna","e":"dan bahwasanya"},{"b":"1.2","h":"2.28","c":"سَعْيَهُ","d":"saʿyahu","e":"usahanya"},{"b":"2.4","h":"4.09","c":"سَوْفَ","d":"sawfa","e":"kelak"},{"b":"3.0","h":"5.2","c":"يُرَى","d":"yurā","e":"diperlihatkan"}],"a":{"g":"And that his effort is going to be seen -"}},"41":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.35","c":"ثُمَّ","d":"thumma","e":"kemudian"},{"b":"1.0","h":"1.61","c":"يُجْزَاهُ","d":"yuj'zāhu","e":"diberi balasan kepadanya"},{"b":"2.1","h":"3.3","c":"الْجَزَاءَ","d":"l-jazāa","e":"balasan"},{"b":"4.7","h":"5.87","c":"الْأَوْفَى","d":"l-awfā","e":"cukup/sempurna"}],"a":{"g":"Then he will be recompensed for it with the fullest recompense"}},"42":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.61","c":"وَأَنَّ","d":"wa-anna","e":"dan bahwasanya"},{"b":"1.4","h":"2.02","c":"إِلَى","d":"ilā","e":"kepada"},{"b":"2.1","h":"3.06","c":"رَبِّكَ","d":"rabbika","e":"Tuhanmu"},{"b":"3.0","h":"4.68","c":"الْمُنْتَهَى","d":"l-muntahā","e":"akhir tujuan"}],"a":{"g":"And that to your Lord is the finality"}},"43":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.5","c":"وَأَنَّهُ","d":"wa-annahu","e":"da